🌈After the fair was over I was certain I wasn’t made for the art fair world. But then looking back I had such an amazing time and Meg some great people and learned so much about myself, my art, and the industry in general. I’m now able to look back fondly on this moment and eagerly looking forward to my next fair! In just under a month I’ll be doing that art fair scene again in #seattle 🌧️at @superfineartfair! Then this October I’ll be back in #dallas at @theotherartfair! 

And then who knows you might even see me in Miami this December at @spectrumartfairs! All I know is it’s been a crazy year so far and while I have no clue what’s in store with the rest of the year, I’m excited to see what happens! 
.
.

🎨🌟 "Fringe" - an abstract representation of the longing to be on the inside, while living on the outside. 🚪✨ This captivating painting delves into the complexities of desiring what appears to be a more fulfilling life, whether it's a large friend group or a coveted job at a specific company.

But "Fringe" reminds us that true fulfillment resides within ourselves, not in external factors. 🌟💫 It serves as a powerful reminder to embrace our own unique journey and find contentment in our own authenticity.

This thought-provoking piece measures 30" x 40" and is created with acrylic on canvas. 🎨✨ Immerse yourself in the vivid colors and dynamic brushstrokes that symbolize the inner desire and the quest for self-discovery.

If "Fringe" resonates with you, it is available for purchase on my Saatchi Art store. ✨ Visit the link in my bio to explore this captivating artwork and discover more of my expressive creations.

Let "Fringe" serve as a visual reminder to seek fulfillment from within and celebrate the beauty of your own unique journey. 🌟💕
.

This piece is a 24" x 24" acrylic on canvas is part of a series that celebrates the simplicity and optimism of mid-century modern design, reinterpreted for a contemporary context. The painting explores the harmonious relationship between form and color, drawing inspiration from the clean lines and functional beauty of mid-century modern architecture. 

The carefully chosen color palette, with its vibrant and earthy tones, reflects the characteristic hues of the era while presenting them in a fresh, modern light. Geometric shapes intersect and overlap, creating an illusion of depth and interaction that invites the viewer to ponder the connections between the different elements. 

Each shape in the composition is deliberate, echoing the thoughtful design of the architectural movement that prioritizes both aesthetics and utility. The artwork is a dialogue between tradition and innovation, aiming to resonate with viewers who appreciate the elegance of past designs while looking forward to the future's visual language." 
#midcenturymodern #homedecor #art #abstractart #abstractpainting #colorful
